com.ihealth.communication.control

Class UpgradeProfile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ihealth.communication.control.UpgradeProfile

  • public abstract class UpgradeProfile
extends java.lang.Object
    Public APIs for the Upgrade serials device profiles

    Clients need to calliHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(com.ihealth.communication.manager.iHealthDevicesCallback) register. When new data from Upgrade device, The Callback{#iHealthDevicesCallback #onDeviceNotify} will be triggered.

      static java.lang.String DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG
      The key of the upgrade result.
      Value:
      0 indicates upgrade failed. 1 indicates upgrade/transmit successfully. Note:
      If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 100, it indicates transmit successfully, device will upgrade itself. If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 101, it indicates upgrade successfully. If the value is 1, device will disconnect automatically, need to discovery and connect again.

      • DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG

        public static final java.lang.String DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG
        The key of the upgrade result.
        Value:
        • 0 indicates upgrade failed.
        • 1 indicates upgrade/transmit successfully.
        Note:
        • If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 100, it indicates transmit successfully, device will upgrade itself.
        • If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 101, it indicates upgrade successfully.
        • If the value is 1, device will disconnect automatically, need to discovery and connect again.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
